SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18
19
in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 11-120 of Title 70, unless there
19
20
is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20
21
A. This act shall be known and may be cited as the “Oklahoma
21
22
Teacher-Led Curriculum Development Act”.
22
23
B. The State Department of Education shall establish a
23
24
curriculum consortium to review curriculum developed by teachers in
24
Req. No. 2855 Page 1

1
this state and make such curriculum available for use by teachers in
1
2
school districts across the state.
2
3
C. The Department shall establish the curriculum consortium by
3
4
August 1, 2026, and include in the consortium only teachers who:
4
5
1. Are certified teachers who have been teaching a minimum of
5
6
five (5) years in a public school in this state; and
6
7
2. Have an Oklahoma Teacher and Leader Effectiveness Evaluation
7
8
System (TLE) rating of superior or highly effective.
8
9
D. The Department shall ensure that the consortium consists of
9
10
teachers from urban and rural schools in the state including, but
10
11
not limited to, a teacher employed by:
11
12
1. A school district with an average daily membership (ADM) of
12
13
five hundred students or fewer;
13
14
2. A school district with an ADM of one thousand students or
14
15
more but fewer than two thousand students; and
15
16
3. A school district with an ADM of two thousand students or
16
17
more.
17
18
E. 1. The consortium shall have an organizational meeting by
18
19
August 15, 2026. Following the organizational meeting, the
19
20
Department, in collaboration with the consortium, shall publish a
20
21
request seeking submission of first-grade mathematics curriculum
21
22
from teachers in this state. The consortium shall review and
22
23
approve for statewide use curriculum that complies with the subject
23
24
matter standards adopted by the State Board of Education pursuant to
24
